// FIX: add a test with a non-empty list and verify process() called for each element
// verify(processor, times(list.size())).process(any())

// Method 2: amount / 100.1 instead of 100.0
// EQUIVALENT? POSSIBLY — but NOT acceptable for financial code
// For formatting only: the mutation changes the divisor slightly
// In most contexts: slightly wrong number = bug (financial: 100.0 vs 100.1 = wrong amount!)
// VERDICT: TEST GAP — add assertion on exact formatted output
// assertEquals("Amount: 50.00", svc.format(5000L)); // exact check kills this mutation

// Method 3: removed log.debug() call
// EQUIVALENT? YES — for most cases
// Debug logging has NO functional effect on the system behavior
// Mutation: removing debug log → system behaves identically
// This IS an equivalent mutant — acceptable to survive
// VERDICT: Add to excludedMethods in PITest config (don't mutate log.debug calls)
// OR: Accept the surviving mutant (annotate method with @ExcludedFromMutation)
